Program: Discovery
Title: Ancient Roman letters home
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p03jrx2m
Last Broadcast Date: 05 February 1998
How some letters to home from Roman soldiers are finally being read. An imaging programme is able to decipher the letter sent from soldiers who had been sent out to Roman Britain. Also in the programme, could a pig organ be used in a human transplant.